Paper: hep-th/0110231

Date: 2001-10-25

Title: Noncommutative spin-1/2 representations

Authors: J.M. Grimstrup, H. Grosse, E. Kraus, L. Popp, M. Schweda, R.

WulkenhaarComments: 7 pages, LaTeX

Journal-ref: Eur.Phys.J. C24 (2002) 485-489; Eur.Phys.J. C24 (2002) 491-494

In this letter we apply the methods of our previous paper hep-th/0108045 tononcommutative fermions. We show that the fermions form a spin-1/2representation of the Lorentz algebra. The covariant splitting of the conformaltransformations into a field-dependent part and a \theta-part implies theSeiberg-Witten differential equations for the fermions.